<a href="mailto:axissglox@hotmail.com">Contact Me</a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uarianwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arianwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/19/02 10:50:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30923.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On Monks Being Perfectly Balanced and Not Overpowered </span><hr size=1> Its not really about *each* CH being efficient, its about total HP, or as Ed put it, margin of error, and about the ability to maintain agro on that char.<br>
<br>
My guilds top warriors can grab and maintain agro much better than even our top monks, and with AE taunt they can usually do it *faster* than an SK.  This is important, if the mob is all over the place, everyone will die, it needs to stay focused.  Here warrior &gt; monk.<br>
<br>
Now, total hp comes into play.  A CH chain is designed to be as efficient as possible, while not allowing enough room for the tank to die from a bad melee round.  This means a chain for someone with less hp has to be faster.  The monk may take dmg at about the same rate as the warrior, but he has less hp.  Also, the warrior will take less dmg during his discipline, during which time the CH chain will be slower.  Over time, its more efficient for the warrior to tank, slower CH chain = less mana used, and on plenty of fights I've been a part of, cleric mana running out was the limiting factor that led to failure.<br>
<br>
BTW, CH is 400 mana base, Specialize Alt. DOES affect it, as do AA skills, focus items do NOT. <p> <center><img src=http://www.webspawner.com/users/ceri2/cerisig.jpg><BR><font size="1"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86991">Arianwen Taur`amandil  53 Druid and Tradeskill Diva</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14796">Ceridwen al`Ban  60 High Priestess</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=323015">Geckonia Chazaliae  30 Monky</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87181">Wenlan Rainjarbot  60 Warder</a></font><BR>
